Base class for systems that extract or aggregate data from entities into a result set.

<p>Data systems operate on {@link ArchetypeChunk}s and populate a result list
based on a query parameter. Unlike ticking systems which modify entity state,
data systems are designed for read-heavy operations like gathering statistics
or building views of entity data.

@param <ECS_TYPE> the ECS domain
@param <Q> the query parameter type
@param <R> the result type

A specialized {@link ArchetypeDataSystem} that processes individual entities.

<p>This system iterates over each entity in a chunk and invokes the abstract
{@link #fetch(int, ArchetypeChunk, Store, CommandBuffer, Object, List)} method
for data extraction. Results are accumulated into a shared list.

<p>Supports parallel execution via {@link #isParallel()}. When enabled, entities
are processed across worker threads using {@link SystemTaskData}, with results
merged at the end.

@param <ECS_TYPE> the ECS domain
@param <Q> the query parameter type
@param <R> the result type

Abstract base class for reactive systems that handle entity-specific events.

<p>When an event of type {@code EventType} is dispatched, this system filters
for entities that match its query. If the entity targeted by the event matches
the system's query, the {@link #handle} method is invoked.

<p>This mechanism isolates event handling logic to entities with specific components,
such as processing damage only for entities with a "Health" component.

@see EventSystem
@see EcsEvent
@see com.hypixel.hytale.component.query.QuerySystem

Interface for systems that require per-tick updates.

<p>Systems implementing this interface will have their {@link #tick} method called
once per game loop iteration. This is the entry point for continuous game logic,
physics, and other time-dependent updates.

@see TickingSystem
@see com.hypixel.hytale.component.system.System

Abstract base class for reactive systems that handle global ECS events.

<p>Unlike {@link EntityEventSystem}, which targets specific entities, this system
responds to events that affect the entire world or don't have a single entity target.
Examples include game state changes, weather updates, or global signals.

@see EntityEventSystem
@see EventSystem
@see EcsEvent

