Lifecycle hook called when the plugin is being enabled.

<p>This is called after all plugins have finished their setup phase and all core
systems are fully initialized. This is the <b>recommended</b> place to:
<ul>
    <li>Register ECS components via {@link #getEntityStoreRegistry()} or
        {@link #getChunkStoreRegistry()}</li>
    <li>Register ECS systems that depend on core component types (e.g., Player components)</li>
    <li>Perform any initialization that requires access to other plugins or core registries</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Note:</b> Unlike {@link #setup()}, all core component types are guaranteed to be
initialized when this method is called. This ensures that methods like
{@code Player.getComponentType()} will return valid values rather than {@code null}.

<p>Example of registering a system safely:
<pre>{@code

@Override protected void start() {
    getEntityStoreRegistry().registerSystem(MyCustomSystem.create());
}
}</pre>
@see #setup()

